      "body": "KMiri doesn't soundly handle `extern fn` or external symbol addresses:\n\n```\n__einit_array=0xffffffff80014fad __sinit_array=0xffffffff80014fcf\nAn uncaught panic occurred: panicked at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/lib.rs:189:20:\nattempt to subtract with overflow\n```\n\nSymbols `__sinit_array` and `__einit_array` are generated by linker, so kmiri should ideally reject unknown  symbols.\n\nBut currently kmiri allocates the symbols even if they don't exist. Miri doesn't have the problem, because such code won't link after  compilation. [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2024&gist=3d8b281041152abaf613a9005dcbfe8a)",
      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "pin": null,
